reviews.reviewText: Very easy to assemble. Also seems sturdy and good for a small closet

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 12, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It’s fine for the price. Nice for small spaces. Fits about 8 pair of shoes. Easy to put together but not super sturdy though. Good enough.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice for the price, assembly is frustrating
reviews.reviewText: Very cute and fits nicely in small spaces. I got this for my daughter but she has limited closet space. This was the perfect size. My only gripe is assembly. You have to line all the pieces up to the holes just so. I would get one piece in on one side then as I was doing the other side it would pop out, but I got it assembled. Because everything just goes into a hole without hardware, it’s not overly sturdy but it fulfills its function.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Simple and gets the job done!
reviews.reviewText: I had a very small space under my side table that was perfect t for throwing your shoes when entering my home. This shoes rack is small enough to fit under there perfectly. It's stackable so I basically only used two of the possible 4 shelves in the set for this space. I'll use the other two shelves elsewhere. The ends are a thick plastic and the bars are hollow metal. It feels like it wouldn't be able to hold a lot of weight (like if an adult sat/stepped on it), but for the job of holding shoes on it, it's perfect. It took me less than 5 minutes to put it together. A simple contraption for a simple job that won't break the bank. 10/10

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Use a mallet, it will be fine
reviews.reviewText: Nice size and decent price. Some folks are saying that it is unstable or flimsy...not so if assembled more forcefully. I put a short 2x4 on the floor as a solid surface and assembled the rack using a small mallet. Tap those metal tubes into the side pieces until they bottom out. Do it evenly so you don't break the plastic.Assembled this way, this little rack is rock solid. Nice size too, fits perfectly in the corner of my closet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
